  "body": "```python\r\ndef get_base_reward(state: BeaconState, index: ValidatorIndex) -> Gwei:\r\n    if get_previous_total_balance(state) == 0:\r\n        assert False\r\n        return 0\r\n\r\n    adjusted_quotient = integer_squareroot(get_previous_total_balance(state)) // BASE_REWARD_QUOTIENT\r\n    return get_effective_balance(state, index) // adjusted_quotient // 5\r\n```\r\nThe division by 5 in the last step makes me feel very uneasy. I suspect it is because there are up to five times per epoch that the base reward can be applied? [but then this is not quite right because of PROPOSER_REWARD_QUOTIENT?]\r\nI would suggest making this explicit by introducing a constant. This would improve readability and also alert someone changing this in the future that these two are connected.",
